The main outcome is a hardened Cloudflare launch surface: the Worker now delegates to the built Vinext handler with asset fallback in [worker.ts](/home/daniel-bo/Desktop/bus-math-v2/cloudflare/worker.ts), the active launch checklist lives at [cloudflare-launch-checklist.md](/home/daniel-bo/Desktop/bus-math-v2/conductor/docs/architecture/cloudflare-launch-checklist.md), and the auth/dev-stack/local-Convex contracts are locked by updated tests and docs. The completed track is archived at [cloudflare_production_hardening_launch_20260316](/home/daniel-bo/Desktop/bus-math-v2/conductor/archive/cloudflare_production_hardening_launch_20260316), and Milestone 6 is marked complete in [roadmap.md](/home/daniel-bo/Desktop/bus-math-v2/conductor/roadmap.md).

Verification passed with `npm run lint`, `npm test` (216 files, 1196 tests), and `npm run build`. The build still emits the already-known `baseline-browser-mapping` staleness warning, and static generation logs the expected fallback when local Convex is unavailable, but the production build completed successfully. Unrelated pre-existing unstaged changes remain in the worktree and were left untouched.


